Week 3 Project: Containerized To‑Do App


Step 1: Install Docker
Download Docker Desktop (Windows/Mac) or install Docker Engine (Linux).

Verify installation:
docker --version

Step 2: Run Your First Container
Test Docker with:
docker run hello-world
This confirms Docker is working.

Step 3: Prepare a Simple App (Todo App) (app.py) file

Step 4: Write a Dockerfile

Step 5: Build the Image
docker build -t todo-app .

Step 6: Run the Container
Start your app:
docker run -p 5000:5000 todo-app

Open browser → http://localhost:5000

Step 7: Optional — Docker Compose (create file docker-compose.yml)
docker-compose up

